{
  "stem": "24163.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There might have been others, but I remember those two quite well.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were fine.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were good teachers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They probably used to hit us now and then, which was standard for-- for European education, certainly, German education.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If you-- if there was an infraction of the rules, or you did something that they perceived to be incorrect in their eyes, bam, wham.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, we got it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I especially did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I probably was not the most best-behaved boy in class, I imagine.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My bar mitzvah was in Gelsenkirchen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Dr.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Gallinen was the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He-- he was a wonderful rabbi.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [INAUDIBLE] Shul, was his name, he taught me my bar mitzvah lessons.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I went through the entire process.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had to learn how to lay tefillin and the whole bit, something I didn't do at home.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I had to learn all these things before I became bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it wasn't the kind of bar mitzvah that the children here are used to, believe me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I could only-- it was a real bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I could only invite a small circle of friends.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it was a family party, a very small family gathering, not the elaborate festivities that they stage today, when-- when children become bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I think it was more meaningful, from a religious point of view, than our bar mitzvahs are today, at least, the ones that we have attended so many times.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The language, of course, that you spoke at home, was German-- only German.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Only German.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Only German.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That was the only language.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Absolutely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no Yiddish at all in our surroundings, except there was some immigration from Eastern Europe into my hometown, mostly from Poland.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
